serializeHeadersInternal

protected javax.xml.soap.SOAPHeader serializeHeadersInternal(IAeAddressingHeaders aRef,
                                                             javax.xml.soap.SOAPEnvelope aEnv,
                                                             boolean aRecipientAsEndpointFlag)
                                                      throws AeBusinessProcessException
Internal method that performs the serialization of addressing headers to a SOAPHeader element on behalf of the various overloaded methods. If the RecipientAsEndpointFlag is true, we serialize the intended recipient as an endpoint reference Otherwise, we serialize the address URI into a wsa:To element. If using a WSA namespace later than 2003, the flag should be false when transmitting to a partner.

Parameters:
aRef -
aEnv -
aRecipientAsEndpointFlag -
Returns:
Serialized headers as a SOAPHeader element
Throws:
AeBusinessProcessException
